      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ASTON WALKER (1) failed to come into contention last start after drifting back at this track, but prior to that won comfortably by 3.5 lengths at this track (22.30) beating Zulu Yallah in a Grade 3/4 on March 20. Boasts three wins from four starts out of this box. Can make amends. RAMBO'S SHOUT (2) scored well last start as odds-on favourite by 3.5 lengths at this track in a handy 27.93 beating Aussie Brook. Fair draw can see a good run and likes the trip. Ran the fastest time on the program in his latest win. Bold showing expected again. ANOTHER JAMES (4) showed little early speed at his last couple, the latest finishing sixth (30.85) in a Grade 5 at Cannington. Solid record here winning 11 races. Leading chance. DITALINI MONELLI (5) profiles nicely here at this trip.",
